<i>♪♪ And you ♪♪♪♪</i>

02:26.355 --> 02:28.813
Wait a minute.
I got another idea.

02:29.816 --> 02:31.432
Here. This one.

02:31.610 --> 02:33.463
She's one of these
big dames, but in proportion.

02:33.487 --> 02:34.487
Has she got class?

02:34.613 --> 02:36.275
Oh, in every way.

02:38.742 --> 02:40.136
I said that,
I would do it. I'll try it.

02:40.160 --> 02:41.241
Do it.

02:56.385 --> 02:57.717
Louie, hit me again.

02:59.554 --> 03:04.345
Uh, hello. Is this Betty?
Um, Betty.. Is this Betty?

03:04.518 --> 03:05.929
Oh, well, I'll tell you.

03:06.103 --> 03:10.347
Uh, my name is-is Joe Clay.
My name is Joe Clay.

03:10.524 --> 03:11.935
I'm a friend of Abe Quine's

03:12.109 --> 03:14.522
and we're here
in the executive suite.

03:14.695 --> 03:16.527
Yeah, Abe Quine.
It's kind of noisy here

03:16.697 --> 03:19.531
but I tell ya he told me that
you are a lovely girl, Betty

03:19.700 --> 03:21.157
and you, uh..

03:21.493 --> 03:24.907
and, uh, he suggested that,
well, you know

03:25.080 --> 03:28.289
you, uh, like to
have a good time.

03:28.458 --> 03:31.747
And, anyway, my agency
is throwing a party

03:31.878 --> 03:33.798
or rather we're inviting
the people for our party

03:33.880 --> 03:37.373
on prince Harun Badul's yacht,
and Abe suggested that

03:37.551 --> 03:40.009
you might be
a very welcome addition.

03:41.304 --> 03:42.795
What, honey?

03:42.973 --> 03:44.430
No, not Abe Badul.

03:44.641 --> 03:47.384
It's Prince Harun Badul.

03:47.561 --> 03:49.723
It's his party on his yacht.

03:51.440 --> 03:53.602
Yes, he's a real prince, dear.

03:53.775 --> 03:57.189
Yeah. Uh-huh.
I thought you would.

03:57.362 --> 03:59.649
Fine. Well, it's berth 23

03:59.906 --> 04:03.240
St. Francis yacht club,
6:30. Right?

04:03.410 --> 04:05.447
Okay and we'll have
a launch there.

04:05.620 --> 04:07.862
All right, bye-bye now.

04:08.582 --> 04:09.823
Magic time.

04:22.846 --> 04:25.338
Here comes number seven.
Let's cast off.

04:41.698 --> 04:42.905
You're late.

04:44.993 --> 04:46.359
You're dressed wrong.

04:46.828 --> 04:48.348
You're supposed to be
a cocktail dress.

04:48.497 --> 04:50.409
You know,
something peekaboo.

04:50.582 --> 04:53.416
You know, sparkle a little.
You call that peekaboo?

04:53.585 --> 04:54.585
Let's go.

05:45.220 --> 05:46.586
Hey, you, wait a minute.

05:47.097 --> 05:48.633
Hey, you! Wait..

05:49.850 --> 05:51.842
Come on, girls.
Come on. Come on.

05:52.018 --> 05:53.018
Hey, you.

05:53.687 --> 05:55.098
Listen, who..

05:55.272 --> 05:57.605
Oh, you must be the new man
from the agency.

05:57.774 --> 05:59.891
Yes, sir. Joe Clay.
You're Mr..

06:00.068 --> 06:01.354
Mr. Trayner.

06:01.528 --> 06:03.440
I see you've already
met my secretary.

06:03.613 --> 06:06.151
Oh, well, not officially.
He was much too busy.

06:06.324 --> 06:07.986
Say, these are fine.

06:08.159 --> 06:09.159
Uh, thank you.

06:09.327 --> 06:11.694
Just fine and dandy.

06:11.872 --> 06:14.910
Well... hello there.

06:55.707 --> 06:57.744
Can I buy you a drink?

06:57.918 --> 06:59.875
Oh, no, thank you.
I don't drink.

07:03.214 --> 07:05.877
Look, uh, I'm sorry
about mistaking you

07:06.051 --> 07:08.043
for one of the other
uh, girls.

07:08.219 --> 07:10.211
So you're the new
public relations man.

07:10.388 --> 07:11.668
- Yeah.
- What happened to Eddie?

07:12.724 --> 07:13.885
Eddie quit.

07:14.893 --> 07:16.850
We liked him.
Why'd he quit?

07:19.606 --> 07:23.145
Well, a little matter of...
personal integrity.

07:26.821 --> 07:28.483
Eddie didn't feel
that getting dates

07:28.657 --> 07:31.570
for potentates was part
of public relations.

07:32.494 --> 07:33.701
But isn't it?

07:35.413 --> 07:37.780
Well, there's a name for it,
but it's not public relations.

07:39.876 --> 07:42.414
Well, whatever it is,
you seem to do it very well.

07:55.809 --> 07:58.426
Oh, boy, wait a minute!

08:00.689 --> 08:01.969
Now, you counted twice
over here.

08:02.065 --> 08:04.307
Wait a minute!
No, there's only four girls!

08:04.484 --> 08:06.020
We had seven!
Wait a minute!

08:06.194 --> 08:09.153
Hey, don't move out!
We got two girls missing!

08:09.322 --> 08:10.984
Wait a minute!
There's two...

08:11.616 --> 08:14.700
Two of my girls
are missing up there!

08:14.869 --> 08:17.737
Two of the young ladies
aren't quite ready to leave.

08:18.456 --> 08:19.456
Aren't quite ready.

08:19.541 --> 08:22.284
I guess I can be congratulated
on a job well done.

08:22.460 --> 08:23.951
Well done. Well done.

08:29.592 --> 08:31.174
Everybody here?

09:34.866 --> 09:36.198
Hi.

09:38.244 --> 09:39.780
Mr. Trayner isn't here.

09:39.954 --> 09:41.991
That's a bit of luck.
You're the one I came to see.

09:42.165 --> 09:43.701
Look, I felt
we should be friends.

09:43.875 --> 09:46.868
So... hello there.

09:47.045 --> 09:49.708
Excuse me. I have to meet
Mr. Trayner at a board meeting.

09:49.881 --> 09:51.721
Look, we sort of got started
on the wrong foot.

09:51.800 --> 09:53.962
It was sort of my fau...

09:57.097 --> 09:58.759
Anyway, I brought
a peace offering.

09:58.932 --> 10:01.015
- Why?
- Why?

10:01.184 --> 10:03.471
Well, because it..

10:10.318 --> 10:14.403
Now, look, we're going to be
working together sort of, huh?

10:14.572 --> 10:16.780
I mean, from...

10:16.950 --> 10:19.033
I'll be up to see the boss
from time to time.

10:19.202 --> 10:21.444
Mr. Clay, that is
your name, isn't it?

10:21.621 --> 10:23.221
Mr. Trayner is the one
you have to please

10:23.331 --> 10:26.119
and he seems very happy
with what you've done so far.

10:26.709 --> 10:28.621
Well, supposing
I wanted to please you.

10:28.795 --> 10:30.627
There's no reason
for you to please me.

10:34.509 --> 10:35.875
Peanut brittle.

10:37.053 --> 10:40.512
Look, you're forcing me to
be rude. I hate peanut brittle.

10:40.974 --> 10:41.974
Excuse me.

10:42.225 --> 10:43.183
Goodnight, Gladys.

10:43.184 --> 10:45.050
Goodnight, Miss Arnesen.

10:51.860 --> 10:53.476
Do you like peanut brittle?

11:23.558 --> 11:24.558
Down?

11:51.044 --> 11:52.764
Getting back to what
people do for a living,

11:52.837 --> 11:53.795
can I ask you a question

11:53.796 --> 11:56.504
that might embarrass you
just a little, hmm?

11:57.342 --> 12:01.336
What spec... what special
qualifications do you feel

12:01.512 --> 12:02.698
that you have for a job
that allows you

12:02.722 --> 12:05.180
to sit around all day
and chat with the boss?

12:05.350 --> 12:06.761
I've heard about your job.

12:07.310 --> 12:09.302
Maybe answer a few
personal letters for him

12:09.479 --> 12:11.892
and accompany him
to parties, hmm?

12:12.065 --> 12:13.705
Spend half your working day
reading a book

12:13.858 --> 12:15.377
while two typists who
get less money than you

12:15.401 --> 12:17.609
do all the work, hmm?

12:18.363 --> 12:20.446
That reminds me,
I forgot my book.

12:31.709 --> 12:33.621
She always carries that book.

12:36.130 --> 12:38.747
I'll tell you what special
qualifications you have.

12:38.925 --> 12:41.245
You're pretty. That's what
special qualifications you have.

12:41.302 --> 12:42.696
That old lech loves
to have you around

12:42.720 --> 12:45.258
to look at and lean on
when he gets drunk

12:45.431 --> 12:47.468
like he did last night,
and who knows what else?

12:47.642 --> 12:50.350
That's what special
qualifications you have.

13:11.457 --> 13:12.948
Oh, uh..

13:13.376 --> 13:14.833
Uh, listen..

13:15.920 --> 13:18.503
I am sorry, and I
shouldn't have said that.

13:18.673 --> 13:21.837
I, uh, I came up here
to try and be friends.

13:22.010 --> 13:24.218
I was going to ask you
to have dinner with me.

13:27.140 --> 13:29.473
Peanut brittle?
I think you must be

13:29.642 --> 13:32.931
the silliest man I've ever met.
Peanut brittle?

13:33.938 --> 13:36.271
Well, I guess you're right.
Let's forget it, huh?

14:06.888 --> 14:08.220
Goodnight.

14:08.389 --> 14:09.550
Goodnight.

14:17.190 --> 14:18.476
Mr. Clay?

14:19.275 --> 14:22.768
I-I thought you were
going to ask me to dinner.

14:22.945 --> 14:23.945
Well, I was. I...

14:23.988 --> 14:26.196
Well, why don't you?

14:27.241 --> 14:30.860
Uh, I mean, my board meeting
won't be over till 7:30.

14:31.037 --> 14:34.121
So I-I wouldn't have time
to change or anything.

14:34.665 --> 14:36.907
It would have to be
some place kind of casual.

14:37.085 --> 14:38.872
Hmm. Mm-hmm.

14:40.880 --> 14:42.587
I know just the spot.
Place Pigalle.

14:42.757 --> 14:44.749
I'll meet you there at 7:30.
You'll love it.

14:46.219 --> 14:47.219
Okay.

14:47.303 --> 14:48.384
7:30.

15:01.526 --> 15:03.142
At a board meeting,
can you imagine?

15:03.319 --> 15:06.903
With all those big old jowly men
staring at me, Mr. Trayner says

15:07.073 --> 15:08.689
"No, I couldn't
get along without her.

15:08.866 --> 15:10.506
"She's always right there
when I need her.

15:10.535 --> 15:12.492
"Especially when I've had
a couple too many.

15:13.162 --> 15:15.199
Takes care of me
like a little mother."

15:15.373 --> 15:19.708
Then he gives me one of those
special proprietary hugs of his

15:20.753 --> 15:23.621
and I suddenly realized
I owe you an apology.

15:24.173 --> 15:26.085
Oh, I'm just as
bad as you are.

15:26.259 --> 15:29.093
I mean, I-I guess
everybody swallows his pride

15:29.262 --> 15:30.969
once in a while
on account of his job.

15:33.099 --> 15:35.386
I had no business saying that
to you in the first place.

15:35.560 --> 15:40.271
Um... hit me again. Not you.

15:40.648 --> 15:41.648
Anything for the lady?

15:41.691 --> 15:42.898
No, nothing.

15:45.445 --> 15:47.152
What do you got
against booze, anyway?

15:47.405 --> 15:49.613
Oh, I just don't much
see the point in it.

15:49.782 --> 15:51.990
Point? Well,
it makes you feel good.

15:52.160 --> 15:53.276
I already feel good.

15:53.453 --> 15:54.693
Anyway, I don't like the taste.

15:54.745 --> 15:55.745
What do you like?

15:55.872 --> 15:57.283
- Chocolate.
- Chocolate?

15:57.623 --> 16:00.331
Chocolate.
I'm practically nutty about it.

16:00.585 --> 16:02.372
Oh, wait a minute.
Hold everything.

16:02.545 --> 16:03.545
Uh...

16:09.260 --> 16:10.260
What did you do?

16:10.344 --> 16:11.344
You'll see.

16:11.846 --> 16:13.115
I think we should order,
don't you?

16:13.139 --> 16:14.380
In a few minutes.

16:16.851 --> 16:18.467
Kirsten Arnesen.

16:19.061 --> 16:20.539
No wonder you're so tough
to get along with.

16:20.563 --> 16:21.599
You're not even American.

16:23.107 --> 16:25.440
Did you ever drive down the
Peninsula toward San Mateo?

16:26.235 --> 16:29.273
Arnesen nursery, that's us.
That was us.

16:29.447 --> 16:31.530
I-I just couldn't take it.

16:31.991 --> 16:35.155
Oh, my father's
a wonderful man, a good man.

16:35.328 --> 16:38.787
but I kept thinking
to myself, "you're pretty."

16:38.956 --> 16:40.618
"You're pretty,
and here you are."

16:41.417 --> 16:42.908
oh, girls know
when they're pretty.

16:44.003 --> 16:46.120
And there I was, blushing unseen

16:46.297 --> 16:48.789
wasting my sweetness
on the desert air.

16:49.091 --> 16:50.332
Gray's "Elegy."

16:51.886 --> 16:53.252
Did you get that
out of this book?

16:53.429 --> 16:54.545
Oh, no, not this one.

16:54.931 --> 16:56.763
That's volume je-la.

16:56.933 --> 16:58.674
Gray's out of volume go-ja.

17:04.857 --> 17:06.473
"World library
of great literature,

17:06.651 --> 17:10.065
Volume five, je to la.
Je-la."

17:12.198 --> 17:14.440
My father gave me those
for my high school graduation.

17:14.617 --> 17:17.030
And he said if I read
all the way from a-bu to ya-zu

17:17.203 --> 17:19.194
it would be the equivalent
of a college education.

17:20.164 --> 17:22.827
Je-la, that puts you about the
middle of your sophomore year.

17:23.334 --> 17:24.334
Ah.

17:25.419 --> 17:26.454
Oh, no, thank you.

17:26.628 --> 17:28.211
No, no, that's all right.
That's fine.

17:28.714 --> 17:31.172
They're special for you.
It's chocolate. Go on, try it.

17:37.640 --> 17:38.847
Oh, it's good.

17:39.100 --> 17:40.100
It is.

17:42.270 --> 17:43.228
Ooh, very.

17:43.229 --> 17:44.720
Yeah, see what I mean?

17:45.189 --> 17:46.976
Brandy Alexander,
they call that.

17:49.610 --> 17:50.726
Say now.

18:06.502 --> 18:08.368
All right, would you
wait a minute?

18:08.879 --> 18:11.963
Joe, it's more beautiful
than ever tonight.

18:12.383 --> 18:13.669
You know something?

18:13.843 --> 18:15.803
You were absolutely right
about that brandy thing.

18:16.095 --> 18:17.011
Alexander.

18:17.013 --> 18:18.173
About it making me feel good,

18:18.306 --> 18:19.616
What are you, chicken?

18:19.640 --> 18:20.721
and I feel wonderful.

18:20.891 --> 18:24.225
You don't feel like asking me
up for a cup of coffee?

18:24.395 --> 18:26.011
Some other time, Joe.
Do you mind?

18:26.814 --> 18:28.414
Anyway, I'm not
quite ready to go up yet.

18:28.566 --> 18:29.846
You want to walk down
to the bay?

18:31.110 --> 18:32.726
Well, why not, Huh?

18:36.073 --> 18:38.486
Let, um...
you do very good work.

18:48.502 --> 18:49.868
Well, there goes
another boatload

18:50.046 --> 18:51.753
out to the prince's yacht.

18:51.922 --> 18:54.209
Another load of anxious...

18:56.886 --> 18:59.253
Ew. I don't see how you can
drink that stuff like that

18:59.430 --> 19:01.296
right out of the bottle,
it must taste awful.

19:01.474 --> 19:03.261
Well, anything
worth having is worth

19:03.893 --> 19:05.885
suffering for, isn't it?

19:06.812 --> 19:08.178
I guess so.

19:12.109 --> 19:13.850
Oh, I like to watch the water.

19:15.655 --> 19:16.757
If you look close, it's filthy

19:16.781 --> 19:21.401
but I like to look further out
where it's clean.

19:22.870 --> 19:24.361
You know what I think?

19:24.497 --> 19:25.829
Hmm?

19:25.998 --> 19:28.206
I think I watch
the water because..

19:29.418 --> 19:32.286
...I expect a sea monster to
come up out of there someday

19:32.463 --> 19:34.955
and carry me down
to the ocean caves.

19:35.132 --> 19:39.843
Mm-hmm. Mom and dad
are a club act.

19:41.263 --> 19:46.054
You know, I mean songs
and dances and snappy patter.

19:47.728 --> 19:48.764
Old-time Vaudeville.

19:48.938 --> 19:51.772
And they're in some loud joint
in Vegas right this minute.

19:52.108 --> 19:53.269
Are they good?

19:55.861 --> 19:59.104
You know, they were on "Ed
Sullivan" a couple years ago.

20:00.074 --> 20:02.031
But you didn't like
that kind of life, huh?

20:04.870 --> 20:10.161
No. I wanted something steady,
something with a little class

20:10.334 --> 20:13.077
like the Trayner
drilling account class.

20:14.338 --> 20:16.204
Joe, don't hate yourself.

20:16.382 --> 20:18.669
It's something you've got to do.
It's part of your job.

20:19.927 --> 20:23.216
No, I want to be a public
relations man, not a pimp!

20:26.809 --> 20:29.768
My-My job is supposed
to be to advise people

20:29.937 --> 20:32.429
how to relate
to the public, you know?

20:32.606 --> 20:37.772
How-How to... make the good
that my client does known

20:37.903 --> 20:42.273
and-and how to help him
find ways to do good

20:42.450 --> 20:45.909
and-and benefit others
as well as himself.

20:47.913 --> 20:50.030
I could be
a garbage man, you know?

20:50.207 --> 20:52.073
A eunuch in a harem.

20:54.211 --> 20:56.328
I'm going to tell
the agency, I tell you.

21:00.384 --> 21:02.501
So I burden you with it.
Well, that's great.

21:02.678 --> 21:04.044
Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

21:04.221 --> 21:05.678
I don't mind.

21:07.600 --> 21:08.761
Short story...

21:11.896 --> 21:14.309
Man meets girl, hmm?

21:15.274 --> 21:16.435
Beautiful...

21:17.276 --> 21:18.392
Sweet...

21:19.862 --> 21:20.943
Nice.

21:22.198 --> 21:25.282
Much too nice for him,
I'll tell you, no, this..

21:25.451 --> 21:28.239
Only kind of girl you really
should bother about, hmm?

21:29.997 --> 21:36.119
Finally, after...
numerous strategical blunders.

21:37.671 --> 21:40.004
He manages to get a date

21:40.549 --> 21:43.758
and he walks her down
to the bay under the stars

21:43.928 --> 21:45.715
and he gets himself loaded

21:45.888 --> 21:47.845
and he cries on her shoulder
like a baby.

21:48.057 --> 21:49.639
Some lover, huh?

21:50.267 --> 21:52.725
Joe, I'm enjoying
being here with you.

21:53.062 --> 21:55.429
After all, you've helped me
avoid my apartment

21:55.606 --> 21:57.222
for the longest possible time

21:57.399 --> 21:59.641
and that's an accomplishment
itself, you know.

21:59.819 --> 22:03.233
The roach kingdom, the whole
building, the whole block.

22:03.781 --> 22:05.675
Do you know that if you don't
leave food out for those roaches

22:05.699 --> 22:06.899
you can't get in the building?

22:07.368 --> 22:09.701
They just pick you up,
carry you into the street

22:09.870 --> 22:11.486
and change the lock on the door.

22:12.122 --> 22:13.658
Roach kingdom.

22:17.169 --> 22:21.413
You know, sometimes I come
down here at night alone

22:21.590 --> 22:25.925
and look at the water,
just to keep from going home.

22:26.095 --> 22:27.095
Yeah.

22:28.097 --> 22:30.297
Well, you don't-you can't
come down here alone at night.

22:30.391 --> 22:33.930
This place is crawling
with all kinds of oddballs.

22:34.395 --> 22:37.684
Oh, they walk by me real slow
sometimes and stare

22:37.857 --> 22:39.849
but they don't do anything.

22:40.025 --> 22:41.025
I don't know why.

22:41.068 --> 22:42.354
Oh, these-you're..

22:46.031 --> 22:46.947
You know something?

22:46.949 --> 22:50.283
I-I dreamt one time
they murdered me...

22:52.538 --> 22:54.780
Over there behind those pilings

22:55.916 --> 22:57.748
and my father came
all the way in

22:57.918 --> 22:59.409
from the Peninsula
in his pickup truck

22:59.587 --> 23:01.874
to take my body home.

23:04.925 --> 23:07.793
And all the way home, he talked-

23:08.262 --> 23:10.379
talked a blue streak
all the way home.

23:11.307 --> 23:14.345
But I was dead and I couldn't
hear him, couldn't answer him.

23:17.187 --> 23:22.273
And the strange thing is
my father doesn't talk.

23:22.610 --> 23:24.602
Oh, he used to talk
to my mother.

23:25.446 --> 23:27.904
When I was a little girl,
he'd-he'd talk to her

23:28.073 --> 23:31.111
in a low, low voice after
I'd gone to bed at night.

23:32.703 --> 23:35.241
But in the daytime,
they hardly talked at all.

23:35.414 --> 23:38.532
They had a very..

23:40.336 --> 23:42.168
...private love affair.

23:43.088 --> 23:46.832
Their favorite toast to each
other was <i>tilsammen I himmelen.</i>

23:47.426 --> 23:48.384
Huh?

23:48.385 --> 23:50.752
In Norwegian, that means
"together in heaven."

23:50.971 --> 23:52.758
<i>To-somonon himlen?</i>

23:52.932 --> 23:54.468
<i>Tilsammen I himmelen.</i>

23:54.642 --> 23:55.928
<i>To-somony himlen.</i>

23:56.101 --> 23:57.842
Get the lilt.
<i>Tilsammen I himmelen.</i>

23:58.020 --> 23:59.727
<i>Tilsammen I himmelen.</i>

24:00.606 --> 24:01.892
Together in heaven.

24:03.192 --> 24:04.478
They meant it, too.

24:05.778 --> 24:07.940
After mama died, he was
more silent than ever...

24:11.867 --> 24:13.449
Almost as though
he'd gone with her.

24:17.414 --> 24:19.371
Oh, well, well..

24:19.750 --> 24:21.616
...gather ye rosebuds
while ye may.

24:22.836 --> 24:24.077
Oh.

24:24.254 --> 24:28.669
Ooh... a little coup-
<i>coup de grace.</i>

24:29.426 --> 24:31.588
Would you believe
it's 2 o'clock?

24:35.891 --> 24:39.180
Ooh... time does not exist
in the ocean.

24:39.353 --> 24:41.436
Well, it will
in the office tomorrow.

24:43.065 --> 24:45.398
I commend thee to the deep.

24:51.907 --> 24:55.150
They are not long,
the days of wine and roses.

24:57.204 --> 25:00.697
Out of a misty dream,
our path emerges for a while

25:01.667 --> 25:03.704
then closes within a dream.

25:19.685 --> 25:23.429
I-I guess... we should be
getting back, huh?

25:39.288 --> 25:40.449
- He come in?
- Yes, sir.

25:44.418 --> 25:45.534
Brad, come in.

25:46.837 --> 25:48.874
Trayner's been trying
to get you all morning.

25:49.048 --> 25:51.415
Well, this is one of those
mornings I couldn't make it.

25:51.550 --> 25:53.132
Oh, those things happen.

25:53.302 --> 25:54.964
He's praising you
to the skies, Joe.

25:55.137 --> 25:56.137
Oh, thanks.

25:56.263 --> 25:58.450
That prince what's-his-name was
so pleased with the whole thing

25:58.474 --> 26:00.807
that Trayner wants to throw
another party tomorrow night.

26:00.976 --> 26:02.888
Wai-wha-
Tomorrow night?

26:03.062 --> 26:06.271
Better call him about it and
congrats on a very happy client.

26:06.440 --> 26:08.898
Look, Brad, could I talk
to you for a minute?

26:09.234 --> 26:10.270
Shoot.

26:10.444 --> 26:14.108
Uh, well, I don't know
how to start it.

26:14.281 --> 26:16.739
I know the Trayner thing
has to be done, you know

26:16.909 --> 26:19.868
arrangements like this have to
be made from time to time but..

26:20.037 --> 26:22.029
But you'd rather not.

26:22.623 --> 26:24.017
Well, I realize
it's part of my job.

26:24.041 --> 26:25.577
It makes you feel dirty.

26:25.751 --> 26:27.228
Well, I don't blame you
for a minute, Joe.

26:27.252 --> 26:29.289
But I don't know what
I can do about it.

26:29.463 --> 26:31.125
Unless we put
another man on there.

26:33.425 --> 26:35.041
Could do that.

26:35.469 --> 26:38.052
Some of the boys don't
mind that sort of thing.

26:38.222 --> 26:40.222
Hey, look, I don't mean
I can't do it. I can do it.

26:40.307 --> 26:43.425
That isn't what I meant.
It isn't that. I just-it-I...

26:43.602 --> 26:46.936
You'd rather not.
Well, let's see now.

26:47.523 --> 26:49.515
Look, not that I won't do it.

26:49.691 --> 26:52.058
It's just the first
account of any size

26:52.236 --> 26:53.356
that you guys have given me.

26:53.487 --> 26:55.695
I think I've got a flash.

26:58.826 --> 27:01.318
Nell, get me
Roger Acton, will you?

27:01.995 --> 27:03.281
That's right.

27:04.873 --> 27:08.457
If Roger goes along with this,
we've got your problem solved

27:08.627 --> 27:09.585
to everyone's advantage.

27:09.586 --> 27:13.421
I don't want this to look
like I'm, uh, complaining.

27:13.590 --> 27:14.790
I just started on the account.

27:14.842 --> 27:16.754
Now, Roger may take
a dim view of this.

27:16.927 --> 27:19.419
Oh, no, no. He'll admire
your integrity, if anything.

27:19.596 --> 27:20.596
Believe me.

27:23.100 --> 27:24.100
Yes?

27:24.476 --> 27:25.762
Thanks, Nell.

27:25.936 --> 27:28.428
Rog, got a little
prob here with Joe.

27:29.148 --> 27:31.231
We put him on that
Trayner drilling account.

27:31.775 --> 27:32.775
Yeah.

27:32.943 --> 27:34.703
Says he heard Trayner
was delighted with you.

27:34.987 --> 27:36.649
Well, here's the prob, Rog.

27:37.489 --> 27:39.526
Oh, that's it exactly.

27:39.700 --> 27:41.111
Says same deal as Eddie, huh?

27:42.244 --> 27:43.860
Oh, he knows
someone's got to, Rog

27:44.037 --> 27:45.932
but let me pull something
out of a hat and we'll see

27:45.956 --> 27:47.288
if it hops for us.

27:47.875 --> 27:48.991
Joe?

27:49.168 --> 27:50.659
- Yeah?
- Hi.

27:50.836 --> 27:52.452
- Hi.
- Come on up.

27:54.006 --> 27:55.463
What in the world
are you carrying?

27:55.632 --> 27:57.999
Oh, just a few things
to go with dinner.

27:58.177 --> 27:59.384
Here. I'll help you.

27:59.970 --> 28:01.381
I was afraid you'd forgotten.

28:01.555 --> 28:04.093
I'm sorry I'm late,
but I was very, very busy

28:04.391 --> 28:05.802
having a couple
with my new client.

28:05.976 --> 28:08.309
Your new.. You didn't.

28:08.478 --> 28:09.998
You mean, you're off
the Trayner drilling account?

28:10.022 --> 28:11.138
Yeah, I am.

28:11.315 --> 28:12.806
Oh, you're a man of principle.

28:12.983 --> 28:16.567
Yeah. Of course, I.. Oh.

28:17.237 --> 28:20.105
I may wish I was back
getting girls for Trayner.

28:20.282 --> 28:22.615
This new guy Ballefoy-murder.

28:22.784 --> 28:24.262
He drinks with both hands.
You can't keep up with him.

28:24.286 --> 28:25.993
You can't communicate.
Thank you.

28:26.163 --> 28:29.281
Hey, this is it, huh?
This is the roach kingdom?

28:29.458 --> 28:30.894
You're feeling pretty good
tonight, aren't you?

28:30.918 --> 28:33.956
Oh, you'll catch up in no time.
Brandy Alexanders.

28:34.129 --> 28:36.837
I got all the makings of the
brandy and the crème de cacao.

28:37.007 --> 28:38.407
We got all the
natural accoutrements

28:38.467 --> 28:39.467
to a home-cooked meal.

28:43.805 --> 28:44.966
You know what's in there?

28:45.432 --> 28:46.432
No.

28:49.895 --> 28:53.309
A chocolate cake
with chocolate icing.

28:55.317 --> 28:57.775
And, oh, here's champagne
to go with the meal

28:58.237 --> 29:01.480
and for me, plain,
unassuming, solid-citizen-type

29:01.657 --> 29:05.617
man of... principle that I am..
the holy comforts of soda and..

29:05.786 --> 29:07.823
Where is it? Ah, scotch.

29:07.996 --> 29:09.407
Now, oh.

29:09.581 --> 29:11.447
This is the roach kingdom, huh?

29:11.625 --> 29:15.244
This is the place where
the roaches reign supreme?

29:15.420 --> 29:16.296
Yes.

29:16.297 --> 29:18.709
Uh-huh. Well, we'll
just see about that.

29:19.591 --> 29:20.752
This is war.

29:20.926 --> 29:22.212
You really are too much.

29:22.386 --> 29:25.720
I just don't believe
in letting

29:25.889 --> 29:27.569
these subversive little
elements take over.

29:27.724 --> 29:29.431
Man of principle,
I salute you.

29:29.601 --> 29:32.184
Salute me with some of that
stuff and go easy on the soda.

29:32.354 --> 29:35.222
Come on, cockroaches.
You come out, wherever you are.

29:35.399 --> 29:37.140
<i>♪♪ You're going to go
to cockroach heaven ♪♪</i>

29:37.317 --> 29:39.434
<i>♪♪ You little dirty
la da dee ♪♪</i>

29:41.863 --> 29:44.355
You-You know something funny?

29:44.741 --> 29:45.701
What?

29:45.702 --> 29:48.910
I didn't really quit
the Trayner account.

29:49.454 --> 29:51.286
- But I...
- Oh, I'm off it, all right.

29:51.665 --> 29:54.408
I just hinted that it was
a little distasteful

29:54.584 --> 29:56.246
and they took me
right off, but..

29:56.837 --> 29:57.837
Well?

29:57.921 --> 30:00.834
What bothers me
is that I didn't..

30:01.383 --> 30:04.592
...demand to be taken off
or even ask to be taken off.

30:04.761 --> 30:06.593
I just hinted, you know.

30:06.972 --> 30:09.430
I mean, I practically
apologized for even hinting.

30:09.599 --> 30:10.715
What do you think of that?

30:12.561 --> 30:16.976
Well, well, Joe,
at least you hinted.

30:17.149 --> 30:19.029
Most people in your position
wouldn't even hint.

30:19.151 --> 30:20.687
They'd be too insecure.

30:20.861 --> 30:21.861
Here.

30:22.237 --> 30:26.823
Oh, to men of principle,
wherever they may be.

30:30.245 --> 30:31.406
Oh, hi, Dottie.

30:31.621 --> 30:33.237
What, are you
spraying in there?

30:33.582 --> 30:35.323
Spray..
Oh, yes, we are.

30:35.500 --> 30:38.538
Well, now, you ought
not to do that.

30:38.712 --> 30:40.472
You get them all stirred up.
What's the good?

30:40.547 --> 30:41.583
Now you made a mess.

30:41.757 --> 30:44.340
You got to think about
other people, you know?

30:44.509 --> 30:47.092
Well, I mean, look,
I don't like to complain

30:47.262 --> 30:48.798
but, I mean,
this is ridiculous.

30:49.264 --> 30:52.428
They don't bother anybody.
They don't destroy anything.

30:52.642 --> 30:53.476
You know they're there.

30:53.477 --> 30:54.829
You leave them alone.
They leave you alone.

30:54.853 --> 30:56.331
You lock up what you
don't want crawled over.

30:56.355 --> 30:57.582
And that's that.
But, all of a sudden,

30:57.606 --> 31:00.474
you start spraying that stuff in
the walls and look at the mess.

31:00.650 --> 31:02.858
What are you trying to do
up there? Run everybody out?

31:03.028 --> 31:04.564
Hey, somebody
spraying up there?

31:04.738 --> 31:07.697
I'm nearly choking
to death down here.

31:07.866 --> 31:10.199
You just come in
off the prairie or something?

31:10.369 --> 31:11.763
People living
in apartment buildings

31:11.787 --> 31:14.245
got to learn to leave
roaches alone.

31:14.414 --> 31:16.414
Now, look, you should see
what they're doing to us.

31:19.461 --> 31:21.181
What's the matter
with you people?

31:23.131 --> 31:24.918
Who's the clown
with the spray can?

31:27.344 --> 31:28.880
What am I supposed to do?

31:29.054 --> 31:31.171
I mean, you've
got them all mad.

31:31.348 --> 31:33.180
They're all-
all crazy, you know.

31:33.350 --> 31:35.467
Well, I-I..

31:35.644 --> 31:37.852
I'm sorry. Well, I..

31:47.447 --> 31:50.110
- Didn't I tell you?
- Hmm?

31:50.826 --> 31:53.443
You've undermined
the whole basic metabolism

31:53.620 --> 31:54.952
of the building.

31:56.915 --> 31:58.998
I'm warning you, Joe.
You better..

32:00.293 --> 32:01.409
What?

32:02.379 --> 32:04.120
You better, you..

32:04.548 --> 32:05.755
What?

32:06.758 --> 32:09.546
You better grow a beard
and move out of town

32:09.719 --> 32:14.180
because-because
those roaches saw you

32:14.349 --> 32:15.885
and the word will..

32:22.149 --> 32:24.857
The word, the word will spread.

32:25.026 --> 32:26.892
And if they ever
track you down..

32:30.157 --> 32:31.318
What?

32:32.284 --> 32:33.991
You'll be a goner.

33:14.993 --> 33:16.734
Oh, darling.

33:56.701 --> 33:58.158
How do I look?

33:58.328 --> 33:59.328
Gorgeous.

34:00.163 --> 34:01.244
And guilty?

34:09.965 --> 34:10.965
Kirstie.

34:11.007 --> 34:13.420
Daddy, I've brought
somebody by to meet you.

34:14.135 --> 34:16.717
I know it's late
and I'm sorry to wake you up.

34:16.888 --> 34:19.050
It was just so important,
it couldn't wait.

34:19.224 --> 34:20.340
Come in.

34:23.603 --> 34:26.219
Uh, Daddy,
this is Joe Clay.

34:26.398 --> 34:27.398
Sir.

34:28.108 --> 34:30.690
Sorry we woke you up,
Mr. Arnesen.

34:31.902 --> 34:34.020
Let's go sit
in the kitchen, Kirstie.

34:35.489 --> 34:37.152
Kitchen is Daddy's
favorite room.

34:37.909 --> 34:40.447
I know this is kind of
a funny time of night

34:40.620 --> 34:42.077
to be introducing
people, Daddy,

34:42.246 --> 34:46.161
but Joe and I... I was
anxious for him to meet you

34:46.333 --> 34:48.667
and we were out driving.

34:49.504 --> 34:52.167
Well, you know how I do things
on the spur of the moment.

34:52.340 --> 34:53.860
I hope you don't mind
us waking you up.

34:53.925 --> 34:54.925
Have a seat.

34:54.967 --> 34:56.379
Oh, thank you.

34:58.430 --> 35:00.171
How have you been, Kirstie?

35:00.348 --> 35:02.385
Oh, that's Daddy's way
of letting me know

35:02.559 --> 35:03.800
I haven't called him
this week.

35:03.977 --> 35:05.343
I've been very busy, Daddy.

35:08.773 --> 35:10.480
What kind of work you do?

35:10.650 --> 35:12.937
Uh, public relations, sir.

35:13.111 --> 35:14.522
Public relations?

35:14.696 --> 35:18.155
Uh, you know, Daddy, it's-
it's hard to explain.

35:18.325 --> 35:22.569
Well, I suppose you might
say my job is, uh...

35:22.746 --> 35:28.117
to sort of help my client, uh...
create a public image.

35:29.836 --> 35:35.298
Well, for an example, uh, let's
say my client, corporation "X"

35:35.467 --> 35:38.801
does some good or something
of benefit to the public

35:39.179 --> 35:42.217
or something that could
conceivably be conceived

35:42.390 --> 35:45.849
as of, uh... benefit to the pu..

35:46.019 --> 35:50.059
Well, my job is to see
that the public knows it.

35:52.275 --> 35:55.518
And what if this "X" corporation
does something bad?

35:58.531 --> 35:59.531
Well..

36:00.825 --> 36:03.533
Well, theoretically,
they don't.

36:04.204 --> 36:05.445
Theoretically.

36:05.622 --> 36:08.831
Uh, well, part of my job
always is... uh

36:09.000 --> 36:15.247
to, um, help my, uh, client
to think of ways to operate

36:15.423 --> 36:18.962
in a way that the public
would, you know, approve.

36:20.637 --> 36:23.755
But if your "X" corporation
makes a mistake

36:23.932 --> 36:25.548
and the thing turns out bad?

36:27.018 --> 36:32.559
Well, uh... I guess then
I try to make it look

36:32.732 --> 36:34.940
not quite so bad.

36:35.694 --> 36:37.046
Well, there's more to it
than that, sir.

36:37.070 --> 36:39.027
It's terrifically
complicated, Daddy.

36:41.616 --> 36:43.573
I don't understand
that kind of work.

36:53.336 --> 36:54.872
You love my girl?

36:57.006 --> 36:58.292
Yes, sir, very much.

37:00.260 --> 37:02.343
Your mama and daddy
live in San Francisco?

37:02.637 --> 37:04.219
- No, sir. They...
- Uh, no.

37:04.389 --> 37:06.927
Joe's mother and father are
in show business, daddy.

37:07.100 --> 37:10.218
They have a-a wonderful act,
I mean, I've never seen it

37:10.395 --> 37:13.513
but from what Joe tells me
they were on "Ed Sullivan."

37:13.690 --> 37:14.806
You might have seen them.

37:17.444 --> 37:18.980
This girl had a fine mama.

37:21.531 --> 37:24.615
Her mama taught her how to
be good, come home early.

37:25.702 --> 37:27.284
I know she remembers
those things.

37:28.955 --> 37:31.242
These days girls think
they have to live in town

37:33.042 --> 37:35.409
but still she
remembers those things.

37:35.879 --> 37:39.043
Well, she's the finest girl
I ever met, Mr. Arnesen.

37:41.968 --> 37:43.129
Look, Mr. Arnesen...

37:43.303 --> 37:45.716
Uh, Daddy,
Joe and I have to go.

37:45.889 --> 37:47.846
We both have to work tomorrow.

37:48.016 --> 37:50.884
Oh. Sure.

37:51.060 --> 37:54.144
Uh, we, uh, hated
to wake you up.

37:56.274 --> 37:58.516
I'm glad you
came by, Kirstie.

37:58.902 --> 38:02.816
Daddy... I hope you like him.

38:02.989 --> 38:04.275
Don't put him on the spot.

38:04.866 --> 38:07.279
Takes time
to find that out, Kirstie.

38:08.953 --> 38:09.972
Nice to have met you, sir.

38:09.996 --> 38:10.996
Same here, Joe.

38:12.123 --> 38:13.763
Daddy, maybe I could
take Joe out this way

38:13.792 --> 38:15.124
and show him the greenhouse.

38:15.293 --> 38:17.000
I'll put on the big light.

38:26.054 --> 38:27.814
Gee, I never knew
there were so many flowers.

38:28.640 --> 38:29.556
Goodnight, Daddy.

38:29.557 --> 38:31.077
- Goodnight, Kirstie.
- Goodnight, sir.

38:31.184 --> 38:32.184
Goodnight, Joe.

38:46.908 --> 38:49.070
Oh, brother,
did I goof that one.

38:49.244 --> 38:50.655
He made me so nervous, I..

39:11.432 --> 39:12.468
Uh, Mr. Arnesen..

39:12.642 --> 39:15.385
...Kirsten and I were married
about two hours ago.

39:37.500 --> 39:39.412
You know what
I'd like to do?

39:41.170 --> 39:44.129
I'd like to go some nice place
and have a drink.

40:14.829 --> 40:16.991
Where is my little gal,
huh? Where is she?

40:17.165 --> 40:18.246
In here.

40:18.416 --> 40:19.416
Okay.

40:22.253 --> 40:23.960
There she is.
I got all the groceries.

40:24.088 --> 40:25.499
Oh, thanks.
You saved me a trip.

40:25.673 --> 40:28.381
And how are you today?
I got you crazy lotion.

40:28.551 --> 40:30.417
She says, "I'm nice
and dry, temporarily."

40:30.595 --> 40:32.211
With the skin
you love to bite.

40:34.057 --> 40:36.174
You're something.
You are really something.

40:36.351 --> 40:37.387
I got to get to work.

40:38.436 --> 40:41.600
Ballefoy is having a bash
for some of the new guys.

40:41.773 --> 40:43.389
You wouldn't want
to go, would you?

40:43.566 --> 40:45.502
I'd love to, honey, but I got to
get up so early with her.

40:45.526 --> 40:47.813
I just thought maybe
you'd want to go.

40:47.987 --> 40:48.945
Well, I would, but..

40:48.947 --> 40:51.781
It doesn't matter. I have to be
there. I'll be late. Goodbye.

40:51.950 --> 40:53.150
- Bye-bye. Call me, huh?
- Yep.

41:00.083 --> 41:01.199
Hi.

41:22.522 --> 41:24.309
Well, I see you got that dame

41:24.482 --> 41:25.939
from <i>Harper's Bazaar</i> to show up.

41:26.109 --> 41:28.897
Mm-hmm. I thought maybe
I could get her to...

41:29.153 --> 41:31.065
Hi, Joe.
Hi, Mr. Ballefoy.

41:31.239 --> 41:32.925
Hi, honey, I thought
we could get them to use

41:32.949 --> 41:35.066
Covington Farms as a background
for a fashion layout.

41:35.243 --> 41:37.485
You know, that country living
we were talking about and..

41:37.787 --> 41:40.655
Tell them we'll furnish anything
they need. Co-operate fully.

41:40.832 --> 41:43.040
Get in there
as solid as you can, Joe.

41:43.209 --> 41:45.020
If we get as much as a mention
of Covington Farms

41:45.044 --> 41:45.918
in the whole layout

41:45.920 --> 41:47.411
I know, I know.
It'll be an accident.

41:47.588 --> 41:49.024
Still, I might as well
confess to you.

41:49.048 --> 41:52.086
I had an ulterior motive
for making the suggestion.

41:52.260 --> 41:53.421
Frankly...

42:01.310 --> 42:02.391
Where was I?

42:02.520 --> 42:03.520
