- Well, leave it open.
- Yeah.

01:22:14.763 --> 01:22:15.924
Oh, yeah.
Here.

01:22:18.559 --> 01:22:21.176
I used to be
a pretty... fancy dresser.

01:22:21.353 --> 01:22:23.720
I wouldn't have been caught
dead with a button off then.

01:22:25.357 --> 01:22:26.393
You're scared, huh?

01:22:26.567 --> 01:22:28.479
No, this is
natural complexion..

01:22:28.652 --> 01:22:29.733
...pale green.

01:22:30.195 --> 01:22:31.436
Nobody will notice.
Come on.

01:22:31.613 --> 01:22:33.320
Well, wait a minute.
We, uh..

01:22:33.490 --> 01:22:34.856
Just, you know.

01:22:35.534 --> 01:22:37.095
Hey, you know, you are
turning pale green.

01:22:37.119 --> 01:22:38.326
Now, will you come on?

01:22:40.080 --> 01:22:41.867
It's facing all the people.

01:22:42.583 --> 01:22:44.700
- Are you sure?
- What do you mean?

01:22:44.877 --> 01:22:46.229
Well, it's facing yourself,
isn't it?

01:22:46.253 --> 01:22:48.040
Look, I don't mind
talking about my life,

01:22:48.213 --> 01:22:49.524
even the most
embarrassing parts of it.

01:22:49.548 --> 01:22:51.289
That's not what bothers me.

01:22:52.926 --> 01:22:54.366
It's... the idea
of standing up there

01:22:54.428 --> 01:22:55.488
in front of all
of those people

01:22:55.512 --> 01:22:57.549
and saying
"I am an alcoholic."

01:22:57.723 --> 01:22:58.723
Are you?

01:22:58.765 --> 01:23:00.347
- Yes, I...
- So are we.

01:23:00.517 --> 01:23:02.745
Now, you've heard us night
after night after night say it

01:23:02.769 --> 01:23:05.102
"I am an alcoholic."
It's a big step forward.

01:23:05.272 --> 01:23:06.638
I know, but it's
funny, isn't it?

01:23:06.815 --> 01:23:08.351
That four months ago
you came to see me

01:23:08.525 --> 01:23:10.312
in the violent ward
and you told me about AA.

01:23:10.486 --> 01:23:12.694
Now, I went to the meetings
and I started listening

01:23:12.863 --> 01:23:15.105
and I've been sober
ever since.

01:23:15.282 --> 01:23:16.523
Kirstie has been
sober too

01:23:16.658 --> 01:23:17.865
just as sober as I am.

01:23:18.035 --> 01:23:20.778
And she has never said,
"I am an alcoholic."

01:23:20.954 --> 01:23:23.162
She even hasn't
been near a meeting.

01:23:23.332 --> 01:23:25.449
She claims she can do
it on willpower alone.

01:23:25.792 --> 01:23:26.999
Can you?

01:23:30.005 --> 01:23:31.837
My name is Jim Hungerford.

01:23:32.841 --> 01:23:34.127
And I'm an alcoholic.

01:23:34.760 --> 01:23:36.217
I'm your chairman
for tonight.

01:23:36.637 --> 01:23:38.173
Now, all I have to do
to qualify myself

01:23:38.347 --> 01:23:41.181
is to say that
I drank too much too often

01:23:41.350 --> 01:23:43.182
over too long
a period of time.

01:23:43.685 --> 01:23:45.221
Welcome to the
regular weekly meeting

01:23:45.395 --> 01:23:47.933
of the Mason Street Group
of Alcoholics Anonymous.

01:23:51.610 --> 01:23:54.569
"Alcoholics Anonymous is
a fellowship of men and women

01:23:54.738 --> 01:23:56.195
"who share their experience

01:23:56.365 --> 01:23:58.152
"strength and hope
with each other.

01:23:58.325 --> 01:23:59.925
"That they may solve
their common problem

01:23:59.952 --> 01:24:02.239
"and help others to
recover from alcoholism.

01:24:02.621 --> 01:24:04.078
"The only requirement
for membership

01:24:04.248 --> 01:24:06.365
"is a desire to stop drinking.

01:24:06.542 --> 01:24:09.330
"There are no dues or
fees for AA membership.

01:24:09.503 --> 01:24:11.665
"We are self-supporting
through our own contributions.

01:24:12.256 --> 01:24:14.999
"AA is not allied
with any sect, denomination

01:24:15.175 --> 01:24:17.508
"politics, organization
or institution.

01:24:17.678 --> 01:24:20.136
"It does not wish to
engage in any controversy

01:24:20.305 --> 01:24:23.048
"neither endorses
nor opposes any causes.

01:24:23.225 --> 01:24:25.638
"Our primary purpose
is to stay sober

01:24:25.811 --> 01:24:28.303
and help other alcoholics
to achieve sobriety."

01:24:29.898 --> 01:24:31.417
Now, we got a couple
of speakers tonight.

01:24:31.441 --> 01:24:33.524
I know you're
gonna enjoy hearing.

01:24:33.860 --> 01:24:35.713
To start things off,
we're going to hear from a man

01:24:35.737 --> 01:24:37.603
who came to us
just four months ago.

01:24:37.781 --> 01:24:39.741
Now, this will be his
first talk at an AA meeting.

01:24:40.701 --> 01:24:41.701
Joe.

01:25:00.512 --> 01:25:01.512
My name..

01:25:04.600 --> 01:25:07.183
My name is Joe... Clay.

01:25:11.148 --> 01:25:12.889
I'm an alcoholic.

01:25:32.461 --> 01:25:33.577
Honey?

01:25:36.465 --> 01:25:37.751
Debbie?

01:25:52.022 --> 01:25:53.022
Come in.

01:25:53.482 --> 01:25:55.064
Oh, hi, Jim.

01:25:55.859 --> 01:25:57.145
I'm sorry to
act like such a...

01:25:57.319 --> 01:25:58.630
Oh, don't be silly.
You should have called sooner.

01:25:58.654 --> 01:25:59.770
Any word?

01:26:00.238 --> 01:26:01.354
Two days and two nights

01:26:01.531 --> 01:26:03.193
and I...
I had to call you.

01:26:03.367 --> 01:26:04.447
I was afraid
that I might...

01:26:04.576 --> 01:26:05.970
Yeah, I know.
Did you tell the police?

01:26:05.994 --> 01:26:07.030
Yeah.

01:26:07.871 --> 01:26:09.237
I-I just..

01:26:09.414 --> 01:26:11.451
I can't see how this
could be happening to us.

01:26:11.625 --> 01:26:13.161
Me too.
Too many drinks?

01:26:13.335 --> 01:26:14.896
Well, a hell of lot of
people drink as much as Kirstie

01:26:14.920 --> 01:26:16.957
and I ever did and
they're not alcoholics.

01:26:17.130 --> 01:26:18.130
Yet.

01:26:18.298 --> 01:26:19.709
A lot of 'em never are.

01:26:21.218 --> 01:26:22.504
It's a lottery, Joe.

01:26:23.595 --> 01:26:26.303
- And you lost.
- Yeah, well, how?

01:26:26.473 --> 01:26:28.510
No way to find out
before it's too late, huh?

01:26:30.268 --> 01:26:31.475
- Joe.
- Hmm?

01:26:31.645 --> 01:26:33.765
You remember how you told
us about Kirsten's obsession

01:26:33.897 --> 01:26:35.457
with chocolate candy
when you first met?

01:26:35.565 --> 01:26:36.399
Yeah.

01:26:36.400 --> 01:26:37.794
Well, a very
perceptive psychologist

01:26:37.818 --> 01:26:39.003
might've told you
then that she was

01:26:39.027 --> 01:26:40.627
a potential alcoholic,
but neither of you

01:26:40.737 --> 01:26:42.048
would have believed
him and besides

01:26:42.072 --> 01:26:43.279
he might have been wrong.

01:26:43.448 --> 01:26:44.814
Joe, how many
strawberries does it

01:26:44.991 --> 01:26:46.823
take to start an allergy
and which is the one

01:26:46.993 --> 01:26:48.484
that gives you the hives?

01:26:48.662 --> 01:26:50.119
Alcoholism is an illness.

01:26:50.288 --> 01:26:51.599
It's pretty hard to
diagnose an illness

01:26:51.623 --> 01:26:52.784
until you've got it.

01:26:53.542 --> 01:26:54.623
Come on, Joe.

01:26:54.793 --> 01:26:55.954
She'll turn up, honest.

01:26:56.128 --> 01:26:57.915
Why did she do it?
Why did she leave?

01:26:58.088 --> 01:27:00.501
- That's...
- She wanted to drink.

01:27:00.674 --> 01:27:03.212
Oh, if she had to drink,
she could drink right here.

01:27:03.385 --> 01:27:04.717
And she ought to know it.

01:27:04.886 --> 01:27:07.469
You're sober.
It's no fun to drink around you.

01:27:08.098 --> 01:27:09.117
Don't you under... it's worse!

01:27:09.141 --> 01:27:11.178
Your sobriety would be
an accusation to her.

01:27:11.351 --> 01:27:14.389
She'd be miserable.
She's lost her playmate.

01:27:14.980 --> 01:27:15.980
And, Joe..

01:27:17.274 --> 01:27:18.606
...listen, uh..

01:27:19.109 --> 01:27:21.897
Don't be too surprised
if she finds another one.

01:27:29.911 --> 01:27:30.911
Look, she loves me

01:27:31.037 --> 01:27:32.323
and you just
don't understand.

01:27:32.497 --> 01:27:33.657
There's no trouble
between us.

01:27:33.790 --> 01:27:35.201
There wasn't any trouble.

01:27:35.500 --> 01:27:36.536
Joe, don't forget.

01:27:36.710 --> 01:27:38.542
For a long time,
long, long time

01:27:38.712 --> 01:27:40.954
booze has been an integral
part of your relationship.

01:27:41.131 --> 01:27:42.567
Now, if she keeps on
drinking and you don't,

01:27:42.591 --> 01:27:44.360
well, you've got to find
a new meeting ground,

01:27:44.384 --> 01:27:45.875
a different basis
for a relationship.

01:27:46.052 --> 01:27:47.452
That takes a whale
of an adjustment.

01:27:47.596 --> 01:27:49.758
Well, I find it
hard to believe this.

01:27:49.931 --> 01:27:51.672
There was one thing
about us, we always knew

01:27:51.850 --> 01:27:53.286
that we were in love.
Now, we knew that.

01:27:53.310 --> 01:27:54.912
And there was no doubt about it.
We just knew it.

01:27:54.936 --> 01:27:56.289
Now, do you understand
what I'm trying to tell you

01:27:56.313 --> 01:27:57.520
that we,
that we had something?

01:27:57.689 --> 01:27:59.646
Well, things like that
don't just evaporate.

01:28:00.275 --> 01:28:03.439
Joe, the night you tore up
your father-in-law's flowers.

01:28:03.612 --> 01:28:04.922
- You're looking for the bottle?
- Yes.

01:28:04.946 --> 01:28:05.965
What did you do
when you found it?

01:28:05.989 --> 01:28:07.070
What? I drank it.

01:28:07.240 --> 01:28:09.360
Oh, you didn't take it back
and drink it with Kirsten?

01:28:13.330 --> 01:28:14.330
No.

01:28:14.539 --> 01:28:15.699
There comes a time
in the life

01:28:15.749 --> 01:28:17.741
of every alcoholic
when the bottle is God.

01:28:17.918 --> 01:28:19.204
Nobody matters,
nothing matters

01:28:19.377 --> 01:28:20.697
but the next drink.
You know that!

01:28:20.837 --> 01:28:21.918
I know I know it.

01:28:22.088 --> 01:28:23.579
I just, I can't believe

01:28:23.757 --> 01:28:25.840
that this is happening to me.
That's all!

01:28:26.843 --> 01:28:28.926
Two people,
seven years.

01:28:29.179 --> 01:28:32.138
Booze, no booze,
drunk, sober.

01:28:32.307 --> 01:28:33.468
Isn't love..

01:28:34.017 --> 01:28:35.017
...love?

01:28:35.977 --> 01:28:37.138
I don't know.

01:28:37.729 --> 01:28:38.890
I was drunk for 12 years.

01:28:39.064 --> 01:28:40.896
I've been sober the last 14.

01:28:41.066 --> 01:28:42.978
All I know is the drunk
world is one world

01:28:43.151 --> 01:28:44.767
and the sober world
is another world.

01:28:48.657 --> 01:28:50.444
Such a lonely person.

01:28:52.285 --> 01:28:53.867
Oh, God, keep her safe.

01:28:55.372 --> 01:28:56.572
Is your little girl all right?

01:28:57.415 --> 01:28:58.747
Yeah, she's..

01:28:59.459 --> 01:29:01.701
...on the peninsula
with her grandfather.

01:29:05.173 --> 01:29:06.173
Hello?

01:29:06.675 --> 01:29:08.166
Yes, this is Mr. Clay.

01:29:08.802 --> 01:29:10.634
Yes, Kirsten Clay.
That's right. Yes.

01:29:10.804 --> 01:29:11.840
- Where?
- Police?

01:29:12.013 --> 01:29:13.675
Where is, Shore Motel?

01:29:13.849 --> 01:29:14.965
Where is that?

01:29:16.059 --> 01:29:17.300
I see.
Who, who..

01:29:17.477 --> 01:29:19.184
Mr. Turning,
is she all right?

01:29:22.649 --> 01:29:24.140
Is she alone?

01:29:24.901 --> 01:29:26.517
I'll be there
as fast as possible.

01:29:26.695 --> 01:29:27.936
Thank you for calling.

01:29:28.446 --> 01:29:29.482
She's in a motel.

01:29:29.656 --> 01:29:31.022
Mr. Turning owns the motel.

01:29:31.199 --> 01:29:32.440
He said that she..

01:29:32.951 --> 01:29:35.113
...came in a cab
and checked in drunk.

01:29:35.287 --> 01:29:37.767
- She's been drunk ever since.
- Do you want me to go with you?

01:29:37.914 --> 01:29:39.892
- No, I'd better go alone, Jim.
- Oh, well, here, take my car.

01:29:39.916 --> 01:29:42.033
- Oh, thanks.
- Oh, Joe, listen, listen.

01:29:42.752 --> 01:29:44.072
At the risk of
sounding preachy...

01:29:44.170 --> 01:29:46.370
No, look, I know now, easy
does it. First thing first...

01:29:46.423 --> 01:29:47.709
No, no,
it's something else.

01:29:47.883 --> 01:29:49.569
Now, she may resent you
intruding on her drinking

01:29:49.593 --> 01:29:50.820
and she may resent
your being sober.

01:29:50.844 --> 01:29:52.029
- It separates you...
- I know that.

01:29:52.053 --> 01:29:55.137
But, Joe... on the other hand,
if you're not sober

01:29:55.307 --> 01:29:57.765
you're not worth a damn to her
or anybody else, are you?

01:29:58.727 --> 01:29:59.727
No.

01:30:09.112 --> 01:30:10.853
- Yes, sir.
- Hello, I'm Mr. Clay.

01:30:11.406 --> 01:30:13.568
Oh, she's in the last bungalow
over there, Mr. Clay.

01:30:13.742 --> 01:30:14.823
Thank you.

01:30:38.350 --> 01:30:39.869
<i>One sliced turnip,</i>

01:30:39.893 --> 01:30:41.475
<i>some stalks of celery,</i>

01:30:41.645 --> 01:30:43.352
<i>add pepper and salt</i>

01:30:43.521 --> 01:30:46.138
<i>and a dash
of Worcestershire sauce.</i>

01:30:46.483 --> 01:30:47.483
<i>My, my.</i>

01:30:47.651 --> 01:30:49.358
<i>What nobility
has to put up with</i>

01:30:49.527 --> 01:30:51.314
<i>just to have dinner.</i>

01:30:51.488 --> 01:30:52.945
<i>I'm glad I'm a rabbit.</i>

01:30:53.323 --> 01:30:54.939
<i>Now, place rabbit
into oven</i>

01:30:55.116 --> 01:30:58.280
<i>and heat oven
to 350 degrees.</i>

01:30:58.620 --> 01:31:02.489
<i>350 degrees?
Too hot for me.</i>

01:31:02.791 --> 01:31:04.511
<i>I just remembered
I have another commitment.</i>

01:31:04.584 --> 01:31:06.450
<i>Please extend my regrets
to His Majesty.</i>

01:31:06.628 --> 01:31:08.244
<i>I bid you farewell,</i>
arrivederci,

01:31:08.421 --> 01:31:10.913
sayonara, <i>and
all that sort of jazz.</i>

01:31:11.091 --> 01:31:12.753
<i>Oh, no, you're not.</i>

01:31:13.051 --> 01:31:15.964
<i>You're stayin'.
I insist.</i>

01:31:16.137 --> 01:31:18.800
<i>Okay, okay,
if it's that important.</i>

01:31:19.057 --> 01:31:24.303
<i>Cook! Cook!
Where's my hasenpfeffer?</i>

01:31:26.606 --> 01:31:29.565
<i>Comin' right up,
Royal Highness.</i>

01:31:29.818 --> 01:31:33.528
Bon appetit,
<i>O gracious Majesty.</i>

01:31:37.993 --> 01:31:40.610
<i>You bonehead.
That..</i>

01:32:04.060 --> 01:32:07.428
- Have a drink, honey.
- Not just now.

01:32:07.605 --> 01:32:10.097
- Oh, come on. Have a drink.
- No, I don't want one.

01:32:10.608 --> 01:32:12.019
Oh, I do.

01:32:13.987 --> 01:32:15.273
You think..

01:32:19.200 --> 01:32:21.442
Honey, do you think
you're about ready to come home?

01:32:24.706 --> 01:32:25.787
Hmm?

01:32:28.877 --> 01:32:30.539
Oh, it's you.

01:32:32.547 --> 01:32:33.663
What do you want?

01:32:33.882 --> 01:32:35.293
I want my wife.

01:32:38.678 --> 01:32:40.419
Sober Joe..

01:32:41.347 --> 01:32:42.713
Milkman's friend.

01:32:44.893 --> 01:32:47.226
Now you got me.
What do you want to..

01:32:47.937 --> 01:32:48.937
...do?

01:32:49.731 --> 01:32:51.814
I was hoping
to take you home.

01:32:57.530 --> 01:32:58.691
I like it here.

01:33:01.534 --> 01:33:03.947
My friends are here.

01:33:06.206 --> 01:33:07.868
You have your friends,
I have mine.

01:33:09.834 --> 01:33:10.834
Have a drink.

01:33:14.798 --> 01:33:16.005
Oh.

01:33:17.008 --> 01:33:18.590
Excuse me, I forgot.

01:33:19.594 --> 01:33:21.836
Shame we're out of, uh..

01:33:24.099 --> 01:33:25.590
...milk..

01:33:27.102 --> 01:33:29.890
...coffee and tea,
orange juice..

01:33:30.897 --> 01:33:32.559
...non-alcoholic beverages.

01:33:35.443 --> 01:33:36.809
Honey, if you'd
just come home..

01:33:37.445 --> 01:33:38.561
No!

01:33:47.789 --> 01:33:48.825
You laid in
a good supply.

01:33:48.957 --> 01:33:50.493
- We could take it home.
- No!

01:33:54.629 --> 01:33:56.336
You have your friends.
You don't need me.

01:33:56.506 --> 01:33:57.792
Oh, honey..

01:33:59.717 --> 01:34:00.924
Joe..

01:34:01.302 --> 01:34:02.759
Kiss me, Joe.

01:34:10.186 --> 01:34:11.848
I taste like gin.

01:34:13.231 --> 01:34:14.231
You never did like gin

01:34:14.357 --> 01:34:16.519
so I didn't
drink it, but..

01:34:17.527 --> 01:34:18.688
Now I'm alone,
so I drank it

01:34:18.862 --> 01:34:20.398
'cause I like gin.

01:34:22.740 --> 01:34:24.732
<i>Tilsammen I himmelen.</i>

01:34:30.748 --> 01:34:34.116
Together in heaven,
like the story.

01:34:37.130 --> 01:34:38.666
Now he doesn't even like..

01:34:40.508 --> 01:34:42.044
...the taste of me anymore.

01:34:53.479 --> 01:34:54.640
Honey..

01:34:57.108 --> 01:34:58.144
Let me get you some food.

01:34:58.318 --> 01:34:59.587
- No.
- Or you're going to get sick.

01:34:59.611 --> 01:35:00.977
- You know it.
- I don't care.

01:35:01.487 --> 01:35:04.446
I don't care. Just... go away
and leave me alone.

01:35:04.616 --> 01:35:06.903
I don't care
about anything.

01:35:12.832 --> 01:35:14.118
I'll be back.

01:35:14.334 --> 01:35:15.370
Don't bother.

01:35:23.551 --> 01:35:24.758
Joe.

01:35:27.555 --> 01:35:28.841
I'm lonely, Joe.

01:35:34.437 --> 01:35:35.803
Have a drink
with me, please.

01:35:37.398 --> 01:35:40.311
- I can't.
- I'm lonely.

01:35:40.568 --> 01:35:42.150
I'll stay with you,
but I-I can't.

01:35:42.320 --> 01:35:45.484
Don't do me any favors.
Can't have a drink.

01:35:45.657 --> 01:35:47.193
Too good to have
a drink with me.

01:35:48.368 --> 01:35:50.906
What did they do to you
down at that AA place, anyway?

01:35:51.079 --> 01:35:52.195
Aren't you a man anymore?

01:35:52.330 --> 01:35:54.322
Can't you hear a woman
calling you?

01:35:54.499 --> 01:35:56.365
I'm a woman.
Can't you hear me!

01:35:57.210 --> 01:35:59.076
- I hear you.
- What're you gonna do about it?

01:35:59.420 --> 01:36:01.540
I heard you, but we've got
our own little apartment...

01:36:01.714 --> 01:36:03.080
No, we haven't.

01:36:03.466 --> 01:36:04.582
I'm not going
back there.

01:36:04.759 --> 01:36:05.875
Never, never.

01:36:06.552 --> 01:36:07.738
I want to be
where people live.

01:36:07.762 --> 01:36:09.173
I don't want
any of your..

01:36:10.807 --> 01:36:12.264
...mealy-mouthed...

01:36:14.018 --> 01:36:17.352
holier-than-thou, do-gooder
boy scouts with their..

01:36:18.314 --> 01:36:20.101
...with their
hot coffee and..

01:36:20.275 --> 01:36:21.857
...and their cold feet.

01:36:22.777 --> 01:36:25.130
I don't want anybody who doesn't
have the guts to take a drink.

01:36:25.154 --> 01:36:27.271
Now go away. Go away.

01:36:33.788 --> 01:36:35.074
I want a cigarette.

01:37:21.461 --> 01:37:22.497
Keep the pack.

01:37:25.381 --> 01:37:27.247
You're not
giving me anything.

01:37:27.717 --> 01:37:29.333
Community property.

01:37:30.178 --> 01:37:31.635
So's the gin.
50-50.

01:37:31.929 --> 01:37:32.929
Here.

01:37:38.728 --> 01:37:39.768
I'm not coming back there.

01:37:39.812 --> 01:37:41.269
You're too good.

01:37:42.607 --> 01:37:44.769
And there's no bore
in the world

01:37:44.942 --> 01:37:46.274
like a goody-good.

01:38:38.287 --> 01:38:40.199
Have some of mine, honey.

01:41:03.307 --> 01:41:04.798
Hello!

01:41:13.693 --> 01:41:15.229
We're closed, buddy.

01:41:16.404 --> 01:41:19.147
- I said we're closed.
- No, come on, please.

01:41:19.323 --> 01:41:21.315
We close at 11:00.
Go on home.

01:41:21.492 --> 01:41:22.608
Oh, please.

01:41:24.161 --> 01:41:26.448
Now look, you, get out of here
before I call the cops.

01:41:26.622 --> 01:41:27.783
Now beat it.

01:41:27.999 --> 01:41:30.116
No, please. Please.

01:41:32.670 --> 01:41:33.706
Please.

01:42:01.073 --> 01:42:02.154
Oh..

01:42:05.161 --> 01:42:06.402
Oh, please.

01:42:06.579 --> 01:42:08.161
What is it?
What's happening?

01:42:08.331 --> 01:42:10.243
Go on inside.
I'll take care of this.

01:42:10.833 --> 01:42:11.833
Go on!

01:42:13.210 --> 01:42:14.792
So you like booze,
hey, buddy?

01:42:18.049 --> 01:42:20.382
I didn't know
you wanted it that bad.

01:42:20.551 --> 01:42:21.837
Why didn't you ask?

01:42:22.845 --> 01:42:25.007
I'll give you
all the booze you want.

01:42:53.417 --> 01:42:54.533
Why?

01:42:55.378 --> 01:42:56.619
Joe, who am I?

01:42:57.630 --> 01:42:59.212
- Joe..
- What?

01:42:59.382 --> 01:43:00.498
Who am I?

01:43:02.218 --> 01:43:03.299
Who am I?

01:43:05.471 --> 01:43:07.087
Say it.
Come on.

01:43:08.766 --> 01:43:09.927
Jim.

01:43:12.019 --> 01:43:13.510
What happened?

01:43:13.688 --> 01:43:15.145
What happened?
You took a drink.

01:43:15.564 --> 01:43:16.680
You're drying out now.

01:43:17.191 --> 01:43:18.251
Listen, your first
two days here

01:43:18.275 --> 01:43:19.753
there was a little
green man chasing you

01:43:19.777 --> 01:43:22.144
around the violent ward
with pruning shears.

01:43:23.531 --> 01:43:25.648
No, no, no.
Don't.

01:43:30.162 --> 01:43:32.449
Got to get up.

01:43:33.374 --> 01:43:35.036
I've got to get my wife.

01:43:35.209 --> 01:43:37.576
No, they went to stay
with her dad for a while.

01:43:42.591 --> 01:43:43.672
I..

01:43:45.344 --> 01:43:47.506
I want her with me.

01:43:49.682 --> 01:43:50.718
Joe..

01:43:54.228 --> 01:43:56.185
Joe, you've got
to stay sober

01:43:57.106 --> 01:43:58.938
even if it means
keeping away from her.

01:44:02.695 --> 01:44:04.607
Hmm?
I can't hear you, Joe.

01:44:06.741 --> 01:44:08.858
I love her!

01:44:10.244 --> 01:44:11.985
Joe, if you
really love her..

01:44:12.163 --> 01:44:13.699
I mean, if you
really love her..

01:44:13.873 --> 01:44:15.284
...then you help her.

01:44:16.751 --> 01:44:17.751
How?

01:44:17.877 --> 01:44:19.243
You set an example.

01:44:19.378 --> 01:44:21.022
Show her that-that
an alky can beat the rap.

01:44:21.046 --> 01:44:22.878
Give her something
to aim at!

01:44:23.174 --> 01:44:24.756
Come on.
Will you do that?

01:44:25.217 --> 01:44:26.217
Huh?

01:44:30.556 --> 01:44:31.888
Oh, boy.

01:44:32.057 --> 01:44:33.410
I should have never
told you about that guy

01:44:33.434 --> 01:44:34.891
with the pruning shears.

01:44:47.990 --> 01:44:49.982
Hello, pop.

01:44:52.495 --> 01:44:54.782
I told you before, Joe.

01:44:55.623 --> 01:44:56.864
Don't come here.

01:44:58.042 --> 01:44:59.453
I've got something
important, pop.

01:44:59.668 --> 01:45:01.751
Something I have
to talk to you about.

01:45:04.089 --> 01:45:06.126
Really, this means
a lot to me.

01:45:13.641 --> 01:45:14.802
Kirs gone out someplace?

01:45:14.975 --> 01:45:16.841
She's gone to
the movies.

01:45:18.354 --> 01:45:19.515
She okay?

01:45:19.939 --> 01:45:21.931
You come here to talk
about Kirstie?

01:45:22.107 --> 01:45:23.143
No, I didn't.

01:45:24.026 --> 01:45:25.983
Tell you what
I came to talk about, pop.

01:45:27.238 --> 01:45:29.275
I've come to square
accounts with you.

01:45:33.202 --> 01:45:34.568
First of all..

01:45:35.079 --> 01:45:38.197
...the $500 that you
lent us that time to..

01:45:38.749 --> 01:45:40.661
...try and get
started again?

01:45:42.002 --> 01:45:44.460
We spent it,
most of it,

01:45:44.630 --> 01:45:46.337
on a couple of benders.

01:45:48.592 --> 01:45:50.529
Really didn't make much effort
to get straightened out.

01:45:50.553 --> 01:45:53.967
I just stayed drunk as long
as the money lasted.

01:45:55.683 --> 01:45:57.595
We lied to you about that.

01:45:58.894 --> 01:46:00.622
And I know you worked hard
for the money, and...

01:46:00.646 --> 01:46:02.228
You started
my daughter drinking.

01:46:02.398 --> 01:46:03.434
Pop, please listen.

01:46:03.691 --> 01:46:06.274
You started
my daughter drinking!

01:46:07.069 --> 01:46:08.505
When she lived here
with her mama and me

01:46:08.529 --> 01:46:10.111
she never drank.

01:46:10.281 --> 01:46:12.648
We never gave her
even one beer.

01:46:12.867 --> 01:46:14.108
You started her!

01:46:14.285 --> 01:46:15.492
Pop, what are you..

01:46:16.161 --> 01:46:18.448
Pop! Don't!

01:46:18.622 --> 01:46:21.160
Are you nuts?
Now, what're you trying to do?

01:46:27.673 --> 01:46:28.789
Pop.

01:46:30.593 --> 01:46:32.209
Sure, we drank together.

01:46:32.803 --> 01:46:34.840
And we did right
from the start, but..

01:46:35.014 --> 01:46:36.255
Where is she?

01:46:37.683 --> 01:46:39.925
She's been gone
three days.

01:46:41.186 --> 01:46:42.427
My girl.

01:46:42.605 --> 01:46:44.267
My girl.

01:46:44.440 --> 01:46:45.647
Pop..

01:46:47.610 --> 01:46:49.693
She went off
with another bum.

01:46:51.113 --> 01:46:53.571
Not the same one,
another one.

01:46:53.741 --> 01:46:55.858
It's always another bum.

01:46:56.869 --> 01:47:00.033
It's always,
"Goodnight, Dad.

01:47:00.664 --> 01:47:02.326
I'll be home early."

01:47:02.833 --> 01:47:04.369
"Goodnight, Kirstie.

01:47:04.793 --> 01:47:07.410
I'll leave the light on
in the kitchen."

01:47:08.964 --> 01:47:12.082
I always turn it off
in the morning, Joe.

01:47:14.303 --> 01:47:16.590
I thought she told me
she was getting better.

01:47:16.764 --> 01:47:19.552
Two weeks ago she was
in the hospital three days

01:47:19.683 --> 01:47:21.640
sick to death
from drinking.

01:47:21.810 --> 01:47:23.927
Can't you tell her
that-that..

01:47:24.104 --> 01:47:25.265
Tell her how well
I'm doing.

01:47:25.439 --> 01:47:27.681
Tell her all about
the new apartment.

01:47:27.942 --> 01:47:29.878
Tell her I'll take her back
any time that she wants.

01:47:29.902 --> 01:47:31.268
She wouldn't listen.

01:47:31.487 --> 01:47:32.523
Well, tell her..

01:47:33.656 --> 01:47:35.272
...Debbie cries for her.

01:47:35.449 --> 01:47:37.566
Then she'd get drunk
for sure.

01:47:37.743 --> 01:47:39.075
I don't know what to..

01:47:40.120 --> 01:47:42.032
I don't know what
to tell Debbie.

01:47:44.708 --> 01:47:46.950
Well, pop..

01:47:47.544 --> 01:47:49.344
...there's some things
we can be thankful for.

01:47:49.463 --> 01:47:53.798
Now, I'm working steady
and I'm sober.

01:47:54.593 --> 01:47:56.300
And I'm starting
to pay you back, pop.

01:47:56.512 --> 01:47:58.469
The $500.
There's the first installment.

01:47:58.639 --> 01:48:00.283
And I'm gonna pay
for her hospital bill, too.

01:48:00.307 --> 01:48:01.307
- No.
- Yes, I am.

01:48:01.308 --> 01:48:02.388
And I'm gonna pay you board

01:48:02.476 --> 01:48:03.495
as long as she stays here
with you

01:48:03.519 --> 01:48:04.537
and-and I'm gonna make good

01:48:04.561 --> 01:48:05.802
for all of
the potted plants

01:48:05.980 --> 01:48:07.187
that I ruined that time.

01:48:07.356 --> 01:48:09.689
I don't need for you
to do that, Joe.

01:48:10.275 --> 01:48:12.312
Pop, you don't understand.

01:48:13.404 --> 01:48:15.646
I need for me to do it.

01:49:33.233 --> 01:49:34.519
Kirs.

01:49:35.527 --> 01:49:36.938
Debbie asleep?

01:49:38.280 --> 01:49:39.987
Yes.
It's after 11:00.

01:49:41.700 --> 01:49:43.692
I didn't want her
to see me.

01:49:46.205 --> 01:49:49.289
- Well, you look so...
- So bad?

01:49:49.458 --> 01:49:51.825
Not as bad as you
imagined I would.

01:49:52.503 --> 01:49:54.540
Thanks for trying,
but I know how I look.

01:49:54.880 --> 01:49:57.042
This is the way I look
when I'm sober.

01:49:57.800 --> 01:49:59.027
That's enough to make
a person drink

01:49:59.051 --> 01:50:00.292
wouldn't you say?

01:50:10.145 --> 01:50:11.477
Joe..

01:50:11.855 --> 01:50:14.097
...I haven't had a drink
in two days.

01:50:15.359 --> 01:50:17.146
Well, that's wonderful.

01:50:18.237 --> 01:50:19.398
It wasn't easy

01:50:20.072 --> 01:50:22.906
but I wanted to talk
to you, so I..

01:50:23.075 --> 01:50:24.316
I thought I'd try
and deserve it

01:50:24.493 --> 01:50:25.574
at least a little.

01:50:25.744 --> 01:50:27.235
Sort of a penance,
you might say.

01:50:27.663 --> 01:50:29.663
You'd be surprised how much
fun you can have sober,

01:50:29.748 --> 01:50:31.489
when you get
the hang of it.

01:50:32.459 --> 01:50:34.041
And you've got
the hang of it?

01:50:34.670 --> 01:50:35.751
I think so.

01:50:37.673 --> 01:50:39.005
Believe me,
it's the greatest.

01:50:39.299 --> 01:50:40.443
Joe, wouldn't it
be wonderful if we could

01:50:40.467 --> 01:50:41.548
go back to the beginning?

01:50:41.760 --> 01:50:43.092
Just erase everything
in between.

01:50:43.220 --> 01:50:45.428
Start all over
at getting excited

01:50:45.597 --> 01:50:46.929
over a chocolate bar?

01:50:51.395 --> 01:50:52.806
I want to come home.

01:51:00.988 --> 01:51:03.150
I-I know what
you're thinking about.

01:51:05.868 --> 01:51:10.158
A lot's happened,
lots of... detours.

01:51:11.957 --> 01:51:13.685
There were plenty of them,
but they were nothing.

01:51:13.709 --> 01:51:16.417
I never looked at them.
They had no identity.

01:51:16.587 --> 01:51:19.045
I never gave anything
out of myself to them.

01:51:19.756 --> 01:51:23.591
I thought they'd help me
from being so lonely

01:51:24.011 --> 01:51:26.173
but I was just as lonely
because love is the only thing

01:51:26.346 --> 01:51:27.532
that keeps you
from being lonely

01:51:27.556 --> 01:51:28.763
and I didn't have that.

01:51:30.017 --> 01:51:31.258
Kirs..

01:51:32.728 --> 01:51:34.288
...there's a little girl
asleep in there

01:51:34.313 --> 01:51:37.477
that would just love
to wake up and see you here

01:51:37.649 --> 01:51:39.857
and all you've got to do
is say the right words.

01:51:40.360 --> 01:51:41.840
I don't know if I have
the right word.

01:51:41.904 --> 01:51:44.271
That's why it took me
so long to get here.

01:51:47.618 --> 01:51:49.234
You see, the world looks
so dirty to me

01:51:49.411 --> 01:51:50.947
when I'm not drinking.

01:51:51.496 --> 01:51:53.283
Joe, remember
Fisherman's Wharf,

01:51:53.457 --> 01:51:54.642
the water when
you look too close?

01:51:54.666 --> 01:51:55.727
That's the way
the world looks to me

01:51:55.751 --> 01:51:56.912
when I'm not drinking.

01:51:57.794 --> 01:51:59.397
I don't think I could ever
stop drinking completely,

01:51:59.421 --> 01:52:00.421
not like you.

01:52:00.464 --> 01:52:01.921
- I couldn't.
- You could.

01:52:02.090 --> 01:52:03.370
If I wanted to,
really wanted to?

01:52:03.425 --> 01:52:05.417
Well, I don't.
I know that now.

01:52:06.970 --> 01:52:09.007
I want things to look
prettier than they are.

01:52:10.933 --> 01:52:14.097
But I know... I know I-I could
be all right if you'd help me.

01:52:14.269 --> 01:52:16.932
I know I could, I'd be all right
if we were together and..

01:52:17.105 --> 01:52:18.374
...and things were like
they used to be

01:52:18.398 --> 01:52:20.014
and I wasn't so nervous.

01:52:20.776 --> 01:52:23.016
I need to be loved. I get so
lonely from not being loved.

01:52:23.070 --> 01:52:24.356
I can't stand it.

01:52:24.780 --> 01:52:26.112
I love you.

01:52:27.366 --> 01:52:28.652
I'm afraid of you.

01:52:28.825 --> 01:52:30.612
I'm an alcoholic.
I can't take a drink.

01:52:30.786 --> 01:52:32.546
And I'm afraid of what
we'd do to each other.

01:52:32.579 --> 01:52:34.241
If you just say
that you'd try..

01:52:34.581 --> 01:52:35.697
I know this sounds crazy

01:52:35.874 --> 01:52:38.161
but I can't face the idea
of never having another drink.

01:52:38.335 --> 01:52:40.188
Honey, one day at a time.
Just one day at a time...

01:52:40.212 --> 01:52:41.212
I can't.
I can't.

01:52:41.380 --> 01:52:42.461
Doesn't it impress you

01:52:42.631 --> 01:52:44.191
that I have been sober
for almost a year

01:52:44.299 --> 01:52:46.040
and I'm delighted
to be this way?

01:52:46.218 --> 01:52:48.050
I'm working steady
and I feel great.

01:52:48.220 --> 01:52:50.240
Debbie and I are living
in a decent place once again

01:52:50.264 --> 01:52:51.880
and it's all because
I'm sober.

01:52:52.432 --> 01:52:53.798
Yes.

01:52:53.976 --> 01:52:55.745
- Well, there's plenty of room.
- Joe, you're strong.

01:52:55.769 --> 01:52:57.556
That's why I know
you can help me now.

01:52:57.896 --> 01:52:59.256
If we only had it
back like it was.

01:52:59.314 --> 01:53:00.850
Back like it..

01:53:01.024 --> 01:53:02.606
Do you remember
how it really was?

01:53:02.776 --> 01:53:05.985
You and me and booze.
A threesome. Do you remember?

01:53:06.154 --> 01:53:07.754
Not that it wasn't
great while it lasted.

01:53:07.823 --> 01:53:09.815
We can have it back
that way again if...

01:53:09.992 --> 01:53:12.700
If I'll drink with you, but
I'm not gonna drink with you.

01:53:13.120 --> 01:53:14.120
It's finished.

01:53:14.204 --> 01:53:15.604
I wouldn't ask you
to drink with me.

01:53:15.706 --> 01:53:17.163
I'd-I'd control myself.

01:53:17.416 --> 01:53:18.702
You can't control yourself.

01:53:18.875 --> 01:53:20.787
You're an alcoholic,
just the same as I am.

01:53:20.961 --> 01:53:22.042
No. No.

01:53:22.212 --> 01:53:23.623
You and I were
a couple of drunks

01:53:23.797 --> 01:53:26.289
on a sea of booze,
and the boat sank.

01:53:26.466 --> 01:53:28.278
I got a hold of something
that kept me from going under

01:53:28.302 --> 01:53:29.918
and I'm not gonna let go of it.

01:53:30.262 --> 01:53:32.003
And not for you,
not for anyone.

01:53:33.307 --> 01:53:35.549
If you want
to grab on, grab on.

01:53:35.892 --> 01:53:37.849
But there's just room
for you and me.

01:53:38.020 --> 01:53:39.020
No threesome.

01:53:52.993 --> 01:53:55.861
I can't get over
how dirty everything looks.

01:53:56.246 --> 01:53:58.408
Try it one more day.

01:54:00.250 --> 01:54:02.333
- Why?
- For her.

01:54:04.004 --> 01:54:05.336
Come and look at her.

01:54:17.351 --> 01:54:20.344
I can't.
I can't.

01:54:26.276 --> 01:54:27.767
You better give up on me.

01:54:29.404 --> 01:54:30.404
Not yet.

01:54:32.240 --> 01:54:33.481
Thanks.

01:54:35.869 --> 01:54:36.869
Goodnight.

01:54:39.247 --> 01:54:40.247
Kirs..

01:54:47.381 --> 01:54:48.713
...take care of yourself.

01:55:00.060 --> 01:55:01.471
Kirs!

01:55:38.807 --> 01:55:40.048
Daddy?

01:55:50.110 --> 01:55:52.102
I thought I heard you
call Mommy.

01:55:54.239 --> 01:55:56.071
You must have been
dreaming, honey.

01:55:56.783 --> 01:55:58.445
Let's go back to bed.

01:56:04.249 --> 01:56:06.707
When is Mommy coming home?

01:56:10.172 --> 01:56:11.788
Honey, mommy's sick.

01:56:12.299 --> 01:56:14.507
She has to get well
before she can come home.

01:56:16.011 --> 01:56:18.094
Is she going to get well?

01:56:20.724 --> 01:56:22.431
I did, didn't I?

01:56:27.355 --> 01:56:28.721
Go to sleep.

01:56:29.357 --> 01:56:30.393
Okay.

01:56:31.401 --> 01:56:33.108
Good night, Daddy.

01:56:33.278 --> 01:56:34.894
Good night, honey.

